[12:55.82]MALCOLM	Dispute it like a man.
[12:57.82]MACDUFF	I shall do so;
[12:59.25]	But I must also feel it as a man:
[13:02.04]	I cannot but remember such things were,
[13:05.26]	That were most precious to me. Did heaven look on,
[13:09.20]	And would not take their part? Sinful Macduff,
[13:12.84]	They were all struck for thee! naught that I am,
