[13:27.72]	Convert to anger; blunt not the heart, enrage it.
[13:31.51]MACDUFF	O, I could play the woman with mine eyes
[13:34.80]	And braggart with my tongue! But, gentle heavens,
[13:38.59]	Cut short all intermission; front to front
[13:42.03]	Bring thou this fiend of Scotland and myself;
[13:45.67]	Within my sword's length set him; if he 'scape,
[13:49.32]	Heaven forgive him too!
[13:51.40]MALCOLM	This tune goes manly.
[13:53.33]	Come, go we to the king; our power is ready;
[13:56.76]	Our lack is nothing but our leave; Macbeth
[14:00.19]	Is ripe for shaking, and the powers above
[14:03.56]	Put on their instruments. Receive what cheer you may:
